                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                <head>No. 638.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Fairchild</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 2, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fairchild</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister, Madrid:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I am much chagrined that our complaints in regard to the interference by Spanish
                    cruisers with American vessels have produced no result.</p>
                <p>Ascertain, and telegraph when aswer may be expected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
